Kano State House of Assembly has commenced move for creation of four additional emirates in the state. At today’s plenary, the Speaker of the House, Alhaji Kabiru Alhassan Rurum read a letter brought to the house for consideration by Ibrahim Salisu and others, requesting the house to start a move for creating four additional emirates in the state. The proposed new emirates are Karaye, Bichi, Rano and Gaya. Hadejia State: Elongated dream of a people New emirates: Borno Assembly makes u-turn FG’s blockage of airlines from Kano is economic emasculation of the North – Rep. Madaki Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin